Date: Be careful not to change the structure of this spreadsheet, because it needs to be parsed by our app.
Exposed: Number of people who currently have the virus incubating, but not yet infectious.
Infectious: Number of people who are currently infectious (not including persons in 'recovering', 'hospitalized', etc.)
Mild: Recovering, mild symptoms: Number of people who are not infectious anymore but are still experiencing mild symptoms.
SevereHome: Number of people who are currently not infectious anymore but are still experiencing severe symptoms but are not in hospital.
HospitalWillRecover: Number of people who are currently in hospital and will later move to RecoveredSevere state.
HospitalFatal: Number of people who are currently in hospital and will later move to Fatal state.
RecoveredMild: Number of people who have recovered, cumulative, after being in "Mild" state
RecoveredSevere: Number of people who have recovered, cumulative, after being in a Severe state.
Fatal: Number of people who have died, cumulative.

Date: Also note that everything you write in this spreadsheet will be published openly on the internet!
Infectious: Inferred assuming 5-day incubation period and 3-day infectious period
HospitalFatal: inferred from later fatalities, missing values extrapolated
